  "Sanctions" : "Respondent understands that this settlement includes a finding that he willfully misrepresented and omitted to state a material fact on a Form U4, and that under Section 3(a)(39)(F) of the Securities Exchange Act of 1934 and Article III, Section 4 of FINRA's By-Laws, this omission makes Respondent subject to a statutory disqualification with respect to association with a member.",
  "Regulator Statement" : "Default decision rendered November 6, 2018. The sanction was based on findings that Hartman twice failed to appear and provide FINRA with requested on-the-record testimony related to an investigation initiated after his member firm filed a Form U5 terminating his employment with the firm for failing to amend his Form U4 in a timely manner. The findings stated that Hartman willfully failed to timely disclose federal tax liens on his Form U4 that were filed against him, in the total amount of $206,409.54 and despite a clear duty to do so. The findings also stated that Hartman twice made false statements to his member firm regarding the accuracy of his Form U4 about tax liens. The findings also included that Hartman failed to timely respond to FINRA requests for documents and information made in connection with its investigation. The decision became final December 4, 2018."
